<item>
            <title>[FLINK-6541] Jar upload directory not created</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-6541</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Steps to reproduce:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;setup configuration property: jobmanager.web.tmpdir = /mnt/flink/web&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;this directory should not exist&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Run flink job manager.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;in logs:
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;2017-05-11 12:07:58,397 ERROR org.apache.flink.runtime.webmonitor.WebMonitorUtils           - WebServer could not be created [main]
java.io.IOException: Jar upload directory /mnt/flink/web/flink-web-3f2733c3-6f4c-4311-b617-1e93d9535421 cannot be created or is not writable.
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Expected:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;create parent directories if they do not exit. i.e. use &quot;uploadDir.mkdirs()&quot; instead of &quot;uploadDir.mkdir()&quot;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Note:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;BlobServer create parent directories (See BlobUtils storageDir.mkdirs())&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
